item.title: Lol noone knows what to do
item.dc:creator: @Superd00d Superd00d
item.description:
@Superd00d wrote:

[quote=“Mr. Despair, post:3, topic:330966”]Go into your sources folder, go to gui.java or EGUI (whatever applies) I’m assuming that heaven-pkz is 317. Search “serverip” and change whatever it’s set to, to localhost.

Some other suggestions:

  1. Make sure your port forwarding correctly, use portforward.com if you’re unsure.
  2. Turn down your firewall and see if you see a breakthrough.
  3. Make sure your No-Ip name is updated and No-Ip is running when you try to login.[/quote]
    and that you have port 43594 usage open.
